The majority, if not all, countries were caught unprepared by the Covid-19 pandemic. No-one in the world seemed to have put funds aside for rainy days – despite the United Nations Millennium Development Goals requiring increased spending on health, especially by poor nations. South Africa is guilty as charged here. Instead of increasing the health budget, spending had been dropping over the years. You then wonder how will they achieve the ANC’s own vision contained in the National Development Plan (NDP)? The NDP 2030 came with high-level targets for the health sector, including raising life expectancy to at least 70...